      "content": "idk, that sounds like just something people say to make themselves feel better. \"defiance\" sounds like so much effort. what's the point of fighting for a tiny bit of warmth when the dark is just going to win anyway? it feels like we're just ants trying to build sandcastles right before a tide comes in. it's just exhausting. it feels more like a mistake than a triumph to keep trying.",
